date_publish: Thursday, March 14, 2013  It was followed by a 2. 9 aftershock at 2 : 12 a. m. and a 2. 2 at 2 : 15 a. m..
text: An earthquake with a preliminary magnitude of 4. 6 was recorded in the North Bay this morning, according to the U.S. Geological Survey.  The quake occurred at 2 : 09 a. m. about 14 miles north - northeast of Healdsburg and had a depth of 1. 2 miles.  There are no reports of injuries or major damage.
title: 4. 6 magnitude quake recorded in Sonoma County.
